	(text "The trigger input uses a wideband RF transformer that galvannically isolates\nthe trigger input to protect the connected signal source. This also limits\nthe trigger pulse width (high pass) which prevents damage to the system from sustained\ninput signals that keep the BJT turned on. The additional diode limits reverse\nvoltage at the base that happens when the trigger signal goes from high to low."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 89.154 165.354 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "48d357b0-692e-4206-bede-9ecbcfb5e995")
	)
	(text "Isolated Trigger Input"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 152.146 96.774 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
				(thickness 0.3556)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "642ea033-1bec-4e84-aff5-e7264a9cffa2")
	)
	(text "Status LED"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 253.492 68.072 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
				(thickness 0.3556)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "77c8cb7e-ea3d-4a18-8ea5-978ecce76c5f")
	)
	(text "The output pulse length roughly follows: C*V=I*t\n\nLes Lab produced a 2ns electrical pulse with 376pF at 200V\nWe will use 200pF at 250V\n-> higher currents -> shorter pulse but same energy\n\nWe optimize for smallest ESI to deliver the stored energy faster\n- No pulse shaping resistors\n- Smallest possible cap package with sufficient voltage rating\n- Multiple caps in parallel with less capacitance for overall lower ESI\n- Optimize the layout for smallest possible current loop\n- Limit current through the charging diode, as it has 25pF capacitance\n  itself that significantly slows down the electrical pulse\n\nWould have liked to use four 47pF caps, but couldn't find any\nthat were in stock with 500V voltage rating."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 14.986 165.354 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "ef56869b-403f-4bcc-83b6-1b56838b8b1b")
	)
	(text "Driver Stage"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 151.1707 22.606 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
				(thickness 0.3556)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "fd3037e0-2470-4b4e-8aa7-e7e19a75e0a1")
	)
